%N A390108 Smallest b >= 2 for which P_{n}(b) = Sum_{k=1..n} b^(prime(n)-prime(k)) is prime or 0 if such a number does not exist.
%e A390108 For n = 6, prime(n) = 13.
%e A390108 P_{13}(b) = b^11 + b^10 + b^8 + b^6 + b^2 + 1.
%e A390108 P_{13}(2) = 3397 = 43 * 79, P_{13}(3) = 60496 (composite), ..., P_{13}(20) = 215065664000401 (prime).
%e A390108 Therefore a(6) = 20.
%e A390108 For n=5 (prime(5)=11), P_11(b) = (b^2 - b + 1)*(b^7 + 2*b^6 + b^5 - b^3 + b + 1) is reducible over Z[b]; thus a(5)=0.
%o A390108 (PARI) a(n) = if ((n==1) || (n==5), return(0)); my(b=2); while(!ispseudoprime(sum(k=1, n, b^(prime(n)-prime(k)))), b++); b; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Nov 03 2025
